{{Infobox Internet exchange point | name = CERN Internet Exchange Point | image = | full_name = CERN Internet Exchange Point | abbreviation = CIXP | founded = 1989 | location = {{CHE}}, [[Geneva]] | members = | ports = | website = [http://www.cixp.ch Official website] | peak = | peak_in = | peak_out = | daily = | daily_in = | daily_out = }}
The '''CERN Internet Exchange Point''', or '''CIXP''', is a historical European [[Internet]] landmark, through which the first pan-European Internet backbone and the first T1 connection to [[National Science Foundation Network|NSFnet]] were established in 1989 and 1990. CIXP is also member of the [[European Internet Exchange Association]].<ref>{{cite web|title=CIXP Membership Status|url=https://www.euro-ix.net/ixps/7-CIXP|accessdate=27 April 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130929023248/https://www.euro-ix.net/ixps/7-CIXP#|archive-date=2013-09-29|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref>
== See also== * [[List of Internet exchange points]]
