{{notability|Book|date=August 2016}} {{unreferenced|date=August 2016}} {{Infobox book | name = Environmental Principles and Policies | image = Environmental Principles and Policies.jpg | image_size = 205px | caption = | author = [[Sharon Beder]] | title_orig = | translator = | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = | language = | series = | subject = | genre = | publisher = | pub_date = 2006 | english_pub_date = | media_type = | pages = 304 pp. | isbn = 978-1-84407-404-4 | oclc = 70232360 | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = | followed_by = }}
The book '''''Environmental Principles and Policies: An Interdisciplinary Introduction''''', written by Professor [[Sharon Beder]], examines six well-known environmental and social principles that have been used at the international and national level. It uses them to evaluate the new wave of market-based policy instruments that have been introduced in many countries.{{cite needed|date=March 2016}}
==Six principles== The six principles discussed in the book are:
* the [[Sustainability|sustainability principle]] * the [[polluter pays principle]] * the [[precautionary principle]] * the [[Social equity|equity principle]] * the [Human rights|human rights principles]] * the [[Public participation|participation principle]]{{cite needed|date=March 2016}}
==Interdisciplinary approach==
This book on environmental policy-making takes a critical and interdisciplinary approach. Rather than merely setting out policy options in a descriptive way, it evaluates policies from different perspectives. This enables readers to gain a thorough understanding of important principles and current policies, and also to be able to apply the various principles and critically evaluate them.{{cite needed|date=March 2016}}
==The author==
Professor Beder was included in a list of "Australia's most influential engineers", published by ''Engineers Australia'' in 2004. She was also included in ''Bulletin Magazine's'' "Smart 100" in 2003.{{cite needed|date=March 2016}}
